    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.75) and **Junior Caminero** (71.31) headlining the lineup as the clear offensive anchors. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a high-floor matchup against Will Warren, where his elite xwOBA metrics and favorable platoon edge override a slight negative park factor. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** remains a must-start despite the park downgrade, as his ability to capitalize on Taj Bradley\u2019s 4.45 xERA and the boost from a top-three batting order position creates significant run-production upside. **Trea Turner** (67.15) and **Kyle Schwarber** (64.13) round out the top tier of the day; **Trea Turner** is particularly vital for our focus on speed, while **Kyle Schwarber** continues to thrive as an elite xwOBA asset at the top of the order against Grant Holmes.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (50.93), who narrowly missed the cut. While **Pete Crow-Armstrong** offers the elite sprint speed we covet for our stolen base category, the optimizer favored **Josh Smith** (59.63) and **Hyeseong Kim** (57.80) due to their superior platoon leverage against right-handed pitching. **Josh Smith** provides a notable 14% boost via dynamic platoon metrics, making him a more efficient play than **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who suffers from an 19% downgrade against Emmet Sheehan\u2019s skill set. We are also monitoring a 34% rain risk for **Caleb Durbin** (69.42) in his matchup against Brandon Young; while he is currently a strong play due to the park and pitching environment, any weather-related delay or cancellation could force a pivot to the bench. Owners should keep a close watch on official lineup confirmations, as the uncertainty regarding **Dillon Dingler** and others\u2019 exact batting positions could trigger minor score fluctuations before first pitch.",
